 28s NAME
 28s        idn2_free - API function
 28s 
 28s SYNOPSIS
 28s        #include <idn2.h>
 28s 
 28s        void idn2_free(void * ptr);
 28s 
 28s ARGUMENTS
 28s        void * ptr  pointer to deallocate
 28s 
 28s DESCRIPTION
 28s        Call free(3) on the given pointer.
 28s 
 28s        This  function  is typically only useful on systems where the library malloc heap is different from the library caller malloc heap, which happens
 28s        on Windows when the library is a separate DLL.
