 55s NAME
 55s        idn2 - Libidn2 Internationalized Domain Names conversion tool
 55s 
 55s SYNOPSIS
 55s        idn2 [OPTION]... [STRINGS]...
 55s 
 55s DESCRIPTION
 55s        The  idn2  tool  converts DNS domains from UTF-8 to ASCII compatible encoding (ACE) form, as used in the DNS protocol. The encoding format is the
 55s        Internationalized Domain Name (IDNA2008/TR46) format.
 55s 
 55s        Internationalized Domain Name (IDNA2008) convert STRINGS, or standard input.
 55s 
 55s        Command line interface to the Libidn2 implementation of IDNA2008.
 55s 
 55s        All strings are expected to be encoded in the locale charset.
 55s 
 55s        To process a string that starts with `-', for example `-foo', use `--' to signal the end of parameters, as in `idn2 --quiet -- -foo'.
 55s 
 55s        Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.
 55s 
 55s        -h, --help
 55s               Print help and exit
 55s 
 55s        -V, --version
 55s               Print version and exit
 55s 
 55s        -d, --decode
 55s               Decode (punycode) domain name
 55s 
 55s        -l, --lookup
 55s               Lookup domain name (default)
 55s 
 55s        -r, --register
 55s               Register label
 55s 
 55s        -T, --tr46t
 55s               Enable TR46 transitional processing
 55s 
 55s        -N, --tr46nt
 55s               Enable TR46 non-transitional processing
 55s 
 55s        --no-tr46
 55s               Disable TR46 processing
 55s 
 55s        --usestd3asciirules
 55s               Enable STD3 ASCII rules
 55s 
 55s        --no-alabelroundtrip
 55s               Disable A-label roundtrip for lookups
 55s 
 55s        --debug
 55s               Print debugging information
 55s 
 55s        --quiet
 55s               Silent operation
